race.comment: Competitive affair to close out the card. RONS FINEST CHOICE (3) is a former Victorian having his first start for the new stable but should appreciate the drop back in company here. Gets Wiggins on board to navigate from the sticky alley and a strong first-up showing is anticipated. VEGAMEISTER (7) was too bad to be true last time out but the form prior was very consistent. Gets some weight relief with the claim and can bounce right back here. SILVER HAMMER (1) strips fitter second-up from the break and should get a cosy run in transit from gate two. Right in this contest. GABBY'S READY (10) boasts a win over this track and trip and may run a race while fresh. QUARRY MAN (8) is a last-start winner who shouldn't be slept on.
